article.headline: Florida Gulf Coast 64, Kennesaw State 57
article.story: FORT MYERS, Fla. (AP) -- Casey Wohlleb had 19 points and Delvin Franklin had a career-high 17 as Florida Gulf Coast beat Kennesaw State 85-73 on Saturday night. FGCU (6-12, 2-3) recorded its first home Atlantic Sun Conference win in school history. The Eagles also received 14 points and 14 rebounds off the bench by Landon Adler while forward Terike Barrowes scored 12 and forward Roman Narmbaye a career-high 10 points. Guard Rob Quaintance added a career-high 13 assists. FGCU led almost the entire way and held off a number of charges from Kennesaw State (3-15, 1-4), which has lost 10 of 11 games. The Owls hit 14-of-30 3-pointers. Ronell Wooten scored 18 points for Kennesaw State, all on 3-pointers. Kelvin McConnell added 17 points.
